<?xml version='1.0' encoding='UTF-8'?>
<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1942-08-05T01:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1942-08-05T01:00:00-05:00" n="51" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d51">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">800.8890/973¹⁄₆: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Afghanistan</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Engert</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Kabul</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1942-08-05T10:00:00+04:00">August 5,
                                    1942—10 a.m.</date>
                                <lb/> [Received August 6—9:22 a.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>47. Please see my next No. 48.<note n="14" xml:id="d51fn14">
                                <hi rend="italic">Infra</hi>.</note> … to reciprocating [<hi rend="italic">reciprocate?</hi>] numerous recent expressions of
                            good-will towards the United States in connection with the establishment
                            of our Legation here, the Department may wish to recommend that whenever
                            possible a little space on steamers returning to the United States from
                            India be made available for reasonable quantities of Afghan exports.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Engert</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>